OL,4,CHospitality: Bullying, low pay and
OL,5,Cburn-out blamed for staff shortage
OL,6, Hospitality workers have called for
OL,7, changes to the industry after an
OL,8, award-winning restaurant in south Wales
OL,9, closed its doors.
OL,11,FShauna Guinn, co-owner of Hang Fire in
OL,12,FBarry, Vale of Glamorgan, said the
OL,13,Fdecision to close after a decade of
OL,14,Fbuilding the business was
OL,15,F"heart-breaking".
OL,17,FShe blamed staff shortages and called
OL,18,Fthe industry "our own worst enemy".
OL,20,FOthers said hospitality must tackle a
OL,21,Fculture of bullying and low pay.
